									<td valign=top><a name="139"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Project Dolphin Update</strong><br>Austnet's <a href="http://www.project-dolphin.nl">Project Dolphin</a> team is currently ranked 59 in the world with a total of 0.3% keys typed. Good work everyone. Of further note is The current leader of the pack Hippychick who is nearing 20 Million keys its taken her roughly 19 months in total.<br><div class=newscredits>November 17th 12:26pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:phoenix@austnet.org">Karl</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="134"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>X-Chat for Windows now shareware</strong><br>Due to the large amount of time and cost in creating new versions of X-Chat for Windows, it will only be available to registered users.<br />
<br />
Non-registered users however can download a 30-day trial of the software. <br><div class=newscredits>September 6th 11:44pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:blase@austnet.org">Blase</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="122"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>mIRC 6.14 Released</strong><br>A new version of mIRC (6.14) has been released. In this version many bugs that have been found in previous versions have been fixed including the annoying timestamp with daylight saving issue. mIRC also now supports ssl connections as this was something greatly requested. More information on the changes can be found at <a href="http://www.mirc.co.uk/whatsnew.txt" target="blank">http://www.mirc.co.uk/whatsnew.txt</a> <br><div class=newscredits>March 7th 1:53am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:none">Rusty^Blade</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="119"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Merry Christmas</strong><br>Season's greetings to all on AustNet, from AustNet staff. May you have a wonderful season and a very happy New Year. <br><div class=newscredits>December 25th 9:51am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:-">AustNet staff</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="116"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>IRSSI - Potential remote crash</strong><br>A new flaw has been discovered in the recently released version of IRSSI (0.8.8). In the wake of this newly discovered vulnerability the authors have released version 0.8.9 which fixes the problem. Get version 0.8.9 HERE (http://irssi.org/) <br><div class=newscredits>December 12th 6:59am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:blase@austnet.org">xmasblase</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="113"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New IRSII Release</strong><br>The new 0.8.8 version of IRSII has been released, and contains new features such as Paste detection, and increased support for sending and receiving large files (~2GB) and also better displaying of DCC file transfer statistics. IRSSI is a popular text-based IRC client for UNIX (See software section for more information and where to download the latest version).<br><div class=newscredits>December 3rd 2:44pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:blase@austnet.org">Blase</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="102"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>mIRC 6.1 has arrived!</strong><br>A new version of the most popular Windows based IRC client is available to download.<br />
This new release contains several bug fixes, interface changes and many other improvements from its previous version (6.03) An important feature implemented with this new version is the ability to monitor any file changes in mIRC (useful for users who wish to prevent any infections).<br />
Also a warning sign will appear when users double-click on a posted Url, this feature is intended to stop the amount of users who are misled into visiting infected websites.<br />
<br />
Users downloading this new and improved version on mIRC will have to bear the brunt, as many scripts for versions 6.03 and earlier might not be compatible with this new release.<br><div class=newscredits>August 31st 3:59pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:blase@austnet.org">Blase</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="96"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>xchat 2.0.4</strong><br>The latest version of the open source XChat IRC client was released today. The change log can be found <a href="http://www.xchat.org/changelog.txt" target="_blank">Here</a> and can be downloaded from the <a href="http://www.xchat.org/download.html">xchat download</a> page. Windows binaries are not yet available. <br><div class=newscredits>July 31st 7:17pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:karl@austnet.org">Karl</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="95"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Project-Dolphin.nl team passes 30million</strong><br>The AustNet project dolphin team has passed the 30 million keys mark and is currently ranked 37th. <a href=http://www.project-dolphin.nl/team.php?tid=390 target=_blank>Click Here</a> to see the break down.<br />
<br />
For those of you that aren't aware of what project-dolphin.nl is, its a key stroke counting "project" that sprung up after the death of the original projectdolphin.com. In order to participate all one needs do is head over to <a href=http://www.project-dolphin.nl target=_blank>http://www.project-dolphin.nl</a> signup for an account download the pulse program and you can start counting keys. <br />
<br />
If you choose you can also join a team such as AustNet's.<br><div class=newscredits>July 4th 5:33pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:karl@austnet.org">Karl</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="94"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>XChat 2.0.3 is out!</strong><br>XChat have released version 2.0.3 of their popular IRC client. The new build includes several bug fixes and also addresses current stability issues. The new release of XChat can be downloaded via our software section for both Windows and UNIX operating systems.<br><div class=newscredits>July 3rd 10:01am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:blase@austnet.org">Blase</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="93"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Updated servers.ini for mIRC</strong><br>A fresh new list of IRC servers for mIRC is available for download. Servers.ini can be downloaded at http://www.mirc.co.uk/servers.ini Instructions of use, provided by mIRC website: “Save the file to the mIRC directory on your harddisk (c:\mirc\ or similar), replacing the old file, and refresh! The server list will immediately be available to you from within mIRC. Have fun exploring some new IRC networks!”<br><div class=newscredits>June 27th 8:27pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:Blase@austnet.org">Blasé</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="90"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Austnet Design Competition Winner Announced</strong><br>A winner for the first AustNet Design Competition has been announced. Nizmo narrowly beat some great competition entries, to win a wonderful web hosting package donated by Maxmax6 Professional Hosting - including one years free hosting and a year's registration of a .net, .com or .org domain. Thank you to all those people who entered the competition and watch <A HREF="http://community.austnet.org">http://community.austnet.org</A> for other coming competitions! <br><div class=newscredits>June 16th 5:31pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="88"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Austnet competition entries</strong><br>Entries have now closed for the first AustNet Design competition, where AustNet users were invited to design a button that could be used to link to the Austnet website. The top 10 buttons are now <A HREF="http://community.austnet.org/competitions/compentries.html">on display</a> in the Community section of the site, and the winner of a web hosting and domain package from Maxmax6 Professional Web Hosting will be announced on Sunday 15th June, 2003. <br><div class=newscredits>June 11th 8:03am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="87"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Cut off date extended for competition</strong><br>Due to the Austnet email problems over the last couple of weeks, it has been decided to extend the Austnet Design competition closing date to 5 pm 9th June 2003. This gives entrants 6 days to get those entries in, to possibly win the great prize of a year's web hosting and domain registration, donated by Maxmax6 Professional Hosting Solutions. Email address for entries is competitions@austnet.org and all details may be found at <A HREF="http://community.austnet.org/competitions/">http://community.austnet.org/competitions/</A> <br><div class=newscredits>June 3rd 10:08am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="84"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Austnet Design Competition</strong><br>Austnet users who would like to have a try at the AustNet Design Competition now have less than 10 days to get their entries in. Up for grabs is a great web-hosting package and domain registration for a year, from Maxmax6 Professional Hosting Solutions. All details for competition entry can be found at <A HREF="http://community.austnet.org/competitions/">http://community.austnet.org/competitions</a> so get your entry in as soon as possible! <br><div class=newscredits>May 23rd 6:35pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:hippychick@austnet.org">Hippychick</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="78"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>Calling all journalists!</strong><br>The new AustNet Ezine is in need of writers of all types - general interest, computers (hardware, software, internet, etc.), arts (films, books, music, etc.), as well as any other items which may be appealing. If you are keen to help out with the Ezine, please email ed@austnet.org with your interests and skills. Some examples of what people have signed up for already can be seen at www.austnet.org/dev/. Don't forget to have your say in the naming of the Ezine at community.austnet.org! <br><div class=newscredits>May 11th 6:23pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:ed@austnet.org">ed</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="73"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New version of eggdrop</strong><br>Eggdrop 1.6.15 has been released and is available for download from <a href=http://www.eggheads.org>www.eggheads.org</a>. As of this release eggdrop now supports the IPv6 protocol. There is a list of changes available <a href=ftp://ftp.ia.us.eggheads.org/pub/eggdrop/UPDATES/1.6/UPDATES1.6.14>Here</a>. For the uninitiated, eggdrop is usually used for 24/7 bots on irc. <br><div class=newscredits>May 6th 10:36am, Submitted by <a href="mailto:karl@austnet.org">Karl</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
								<tr>
									<td valign=top><a name="71"><img src="../images/dot_orange.gif" height="8" width="8" vspace="5"></a></td>
									<td><strong>New AustNet project</strong><br>AustNet Public Relations team has found another project that the austnet community is invited to take part in if they wish. The new project is <a href=http://www.project-dolphin.nl target=_blank>Project Dolphin</a>. (It's not exactly the same as the previous one). The goal is still the same to count your keystrokes. However this site is better than the previous project-orca which was missing a lot of features. If you decide you want to take part head over to <a href=http://www.project-dolphin.nl target="_blank">http://www.project-dolphin.nl</a> sign up for an account, join the AustNet team and download the client to start counting your key strokes. Happy typing!<br><div class=newscredits>May 4th 2:56pm, Submitted by <a href="mailto:karl@austnet.org">Karl</a></div></td></tr>
<table width="100%" cellpadding=2>
